-- Bigger Euro Firewall Would Calm Markets, EFSF Chief Tells Focus
-- B y   N a o m i   K r e s g e
-- 2012-03-25T12:38:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-25/bigger-euro-firewall-would-calm-markets-efsf-chief-tells-focus.html
Expanding the euro-area’s rescue
funds would calm markets, Klaus Regling, chief executive officer
of the European Financial Stability Facility, told  Focus 
magazine in an interview.  The majority of market participants don’t believe the
crisis is over and expect further downgrades this year, the
magazine cited Regling as saying in an e-mailed preview of its
article.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Naomi Kresge in Berlin at 
